The paper deals with revenue maximization in auction settings, which falls under game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The use of LPs to capture approximation factors suggests a focus on optimization and algorithms (cs.DS), while the mention of value distributions and correlation gaps suggests a statistical or probabilistic approach (cs.IT). Finally, the mention of free-order prophet inequalities suggests a connection to online algorithms and learning (cs.LG).
